      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "You could do that but in that case you need to keep the backend up an d running and available all the time. Users need to trust you 100% and will not have any way to exit etc if something goes wrong. Proof existing on chain even helps with some historical data while it's not that much. \n\nIn summary you can think like \"why layer 2 solutions send their transactions to ether\" If you are doing something completely independent from mina than you can just run everything off-chain since you don't require any settlement on chain.",
